.TH HSH 1 "DEC 2022"

.SH NAME
hsh \- Holberton Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBhsh\fP is a simple shell program written in C, providing a basic command-line interface for users to execute commands.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display this help message and exit.

.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Display version information and exit.

.SH COMMANDS
.P
hsh supports the following built-in commands:

.IP "cat [options] file..."
Display the contents of one or more files.

.IP "chmod [options] mode file..."
Change file permissions.

.IP "chown [options] owner:group file..."
Change file owner and group.

.IP "clear"
Removes all text and previous commands from the terminal, giving you a blank screen.

.IP "cp [options] source destination"
Copy files or directories from source to destination.

.IP "echo [options] [string...]"
Display a message or variable.

.IP "exit [status]"
Exit the shell with an optional status code.

.IP "grep [options] pattern [file...]"
Search for a pattern in one or more files.

.IP "kill [options] pid"
Send a signal to a process.

.IP "less [options] file..."
Views text files, allowing you to navigate through the file, search for specific content, and perform various operations.

.IP "ls [options] [directory]"
List files and directories in the specified directory. If no directory is provided, list the contents of the current directory.

.IP "man"
Display the manual pages for commands, utilities, and other system-related information.

.IP "mkdir [options] directory..."
Create directories with the specified names.

.IP "mv [options] source destination"
Move (rename) files or directories from source to destination.

.IP "pipeline"
Execute a pipeline of commands, connecting the output of one to the input of the next.

.IP "ps [options]"
Display information about active processes.

.IP "rm [options] file..."
Remove (delete) files or directories.

.IP "touch [options] file..."
Creates an empty file.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
To run a command:
.B simple_shell command arg1 arg2

.TP
To create a pipeline:
.B simple_shell command1 | command2

.TP
To change the current working directory:
.B simple_shell cd /path/to/directory

.TP
To list files in a directory:
.B simple_shell ls /path/to/directory

.TP
To copy a file:
.B simple_shell cp file.txt /path/to/destination

.TP
To remove a file:
.B simple_shell rm file.txt
.SH USAGE
To run the shell, simply execute the \fBhsh\fP binary.

.B
$ hsh

.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
The shell operates in interactive mode when executed without any arguments. In interactive mode, the shell displays a command prompt and waits for user input.

.B
$ hsh
$

.SH COMMAND EXECUTION
The shell can execute external commands and built-in commands.

External commands are executed by providing the command name and any required arguments.

.B
$ ls -l

Built-in commands are internal to the shell and include:

.IP "exit"
Exit the shell.

.B
$ exit

.SH PATH RESOLUTION
The shell searches for executable commands in the following directories:

.IP "/usr/local/bin/"
.IP "/usr/bin/"
.IP "/bin/"
.IP "/usr/local/games/"
.IP "/usr/games/"

If a command is not found in these directories, an error is displayed.

.SH ERROR HANDLING
The shell provides basic error messages for command execution failures.

